                "content": "## World Map\n\n<img class=\"img-thumbnail\" src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/NZzMwvs1q4yBAr0A-00dZgunhnQpEAioX2SYJ5oVtYS5TNbbayXAceunzzyTwt5MOqnfWyUnPjXKCu1dnL-2PN6qy8Yx5BHZXfdAug3XcnMEfIvdSjcwgFFOsipI71rWoveSgl6Q0GafL17SW8_38P1EEhMRYMV0k9nuMoBWpmeTjb1E9GQQan4AYGZDFH1TVqcwBVEHgDmuGxr4aSp33joThtSUvVvn-RI5ifLE1CoZPI_kXa8j5a9JAJpZrMwJqrE-YHlRXH0IGJsXpZNXZj8OVxVDqg_XprdkKZEO0hLoUAx5s-yqJih1TLpgaOJu-azRJKDUW1J9Uz_Qtjr0v3k0dVXkxFSnuoHoMPVhylKOkh1dcNRXU5I4PajRbs2vDm6W8cUJJZilzGZBt5HgRjrxMTq-wKvFTG5Eqwx90b_r8up-atG64hwzkI9b72Y4S8_ZDH294xK-n4RF8WKFHfh0JmGs5LXUtu725rxgMGNQnCYeoIHshifBxmd_eLM9iNPeBGzG6tPi_FVazVuDmwVaoIu37G3UyP4moSR80GE=w2820-h2114-no\" width=\"100%\">\n\n## Details\n\nThe TaurÃ« forest contains the elves, and wood elves, high elves, and dark elves vie for control (with a fair amount of detail fleshed out, so I can expand more if you like). The dwarves are unified for the most part in the mountains to the west, and the desolate and deserted frozen tundra of Khan A'dah stretch out to the north.\n\nToernÃ«, the largest human city, serves as a cultural and economic hub for the entire region. The humans, as humans do, have sort of spread out all over, so there's not really any sort of central government for them. The Dreadful own Westbury, and for the moment seem content with the one city.\n\nThe Mandius wastes are harsh and inhospitable deserts that contain only the toughest sorts, slavers and treasure hunters and kobolds and whatnot. There are rumors and stories of massive treasure beneath the sands, for those with the ability to find it.\n\nThe island at the bottom is Ishoy, covered in jungle and mystery. Also, dinosaurs. That's been the hub for my nautical campaign, which is exploring the area south of this map.",
